-- A.S Roma Receives Six Acquisition Offers for Soccer Club, Messaggero Says
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2010-11-04T07:13:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/a-s-roma-receives-six-acquisition-offers-for-soccer-club-messaggero-says.html
Italian soccer club  A.S. Roma SpA 
received six acquisition offers, Il Messaggero reported, citing
unidentified people familiar with the matter.  Aabar Investments PJSC, the Abu Dhabi government controlled
company, and a financial holding linked to Libya’s sovereign
wealth fund presented their offers to Roma’s adviser Rothschild,
according to the newspaper.  Other offers came from China and Rome businessman  Giampaolo Angelucci , while  Naguib Sawiris   decided not to present a bid,
Messaggero said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Lorenzo Totaro  in Rome at 
